<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="34" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,266,612]" pageId="13" pageNumber="34">
Males winged. Scrobe absent. Mandible reduced in size. Basal cavity of mandible extending to its front face and visible in full-face view. Notauli impressed on mesoscutum in most species. Mesepimeron bears distinct (epimeral) lobe posterodorsally, lobe covering mesothoracic spiracle and appearing to form isolated plate. Dorsolateral corner of petiole in anterior view without distinct projections. Dorsal margin of petiole in anterior view gently rounded, not forming a conical or pointed apex. Apical margin of abdominal tergum VIII occasionally featuring down-curved projection (
<figureCitation box="[717,780,466,492]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="15.[151,255,1850,1874]" captionTargetBox="[162,1422,205,1811]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[155,1432,197,1823]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 8. Males of Ponerinae. a – e, Odontomachus coquereli (CASENT 0049797). f, Leptogenys sp. (CASENT 0114506). (a) head to abdomen in lateral view; (b) petiole in anterior view; (c) head to abdomen in dorsal view; (d) head in full-face view; (e, f) apical portion of the abdomen in dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/274011/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="34">
Fig. 
<number box="[766,780,466,492]" pageId="13" pageNumber="34" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
f). Jugal lobe of hind wing absent in most species. Each middle and hind tibia with two spurs. Pretarsal claw multidentate to pectinate.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="34" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,266,612]" pageId="13" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,314,546,572]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="34">Remarks.</emphasis>
The multidentate or pectinate claws (
<figureCitation box="[768,839,546,572]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="14.[151,255,1831,1855]" captionTargetBox="[160,1420,181,1820]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[157,1429,173,1827]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 7. Male Leptogenys Mad 02 (CASENT 0496777). (a) head to abdomen in profile; (b) pretarsal claw; (c) tibial spurs on hind leg; (d) head to abdomen in dorsal view; (e) head in full-face view; (f) forewing; (g) hind wing." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/274010/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="34">
Fig. 
<number box="[824,839,546,572]" pageId="13" pageNumber="34" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
b) easily separate this genus from other 
<collectingCountry box="[1322,1436,546,572]" name="Madagascar" pageId="13" pageNumber="34">Malagasy</collectingCountry>
ponerine males.
</paragraph>
